          .privacy-content
            h2 1. Introduction
            p Ciphergram LTD ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website https://ciphergram.io (the "Site") or use our services.

            h2 2. Information We Collect
            h3 2.1 Personal Information
            p We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, including:
            ul
              li Name and contact information (email address, phone number)
              li Company information and job title
              li Information provided through contact forms or service inquiries
              li Communication preferences

            h3 2.2 Automatically Collected Information
            p We may automatically collect certain information about your device and usage of our Site, including:
            ul
              li IP address and location data
              li Browser type and version
              li Operating system
              li Pages visited and time spent on our Site
              li Referring website information
              li Cookies and similar tracking technologies

            h2 3. How We Use Your Information
            p We use the information we collect to:
            ul
              li Provide, operate, and maintain our services
              li Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support
              li Send you technical notices, updates, and administrative messages
              li Improve our website and services
              li Analyze usage patterns and trends
              li Comply with legal obligations
              li Protect against fraud and unauthorized access

            h2 4. Information Sharing and Disclosure
            p We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties except in the following circumstances:
            ul
              li With your explicit consent
              li To trusted service providers who assist us in operating our website and conducting our business
              li When required by law or to protect our rights
              li In connection with a business transfer or acquisition

            h2 5. Data Security
            p We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.

            h2 6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
            p Our website uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience. You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences. Disabling cookies may affect the functionality of our website.

            h2 7. Third-Party Links
            p Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.

            h2 8. Your Rights and Choices
            p Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:
            ul
              li The right to access your personal information
              li The right to correct inaccurate information
              li The right to delete your personal information
              li The right to restrict or object to processing
              li The right to data portability
              li The right to withdraw consent

            h2 9. Children's Privacy
            p Our services are not directed to children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.

            h2 10. Florida State Law Compliance
            p This Privacy Policy complies with applicable Florida state laws, including:
            ul
              li Florida Information Protection Act (FIPA)
              li Florida's data breach notification requirements
              li Any other applicable state privacy regulations

            h2 11. International Data Transfers
            p If you are accessing our services from outside the United States, please be aware that your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States where our servers are located.

            h2 12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
            p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. Your continued use of our services after any modifications constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

            h2 13. Contact Information
            p If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:
            .contact-info
              p
                strong Ciphergram LTD
                br
                | Email: info@ciphergram.io
                br
                | Website: https://ciphergram.io
                br
                | Address: Chicago, Illinois, United States

            h2 14. Effective Date
            p This Privacy Policy is effective as of January 15, 2025, and will remain in effect except with respect to any changes in its provisions in the future, which will be in effect immediately after being posted on this page.

